    article.main
        .om
            section
                h1 CONCEPTUAL MODEL
            aside Maxim Sokhatsky
                time 1 SEP 2018
            p.
                The conceptual model of theorem proving system is presented here as a set of:
                1) calculi with its categorical models; 2) programs or base libraries; and
                3) program transformations: type checking, compilation, type erasure,
                code extraction, optimization, etc. The overall system is for math and
                general purpose programming with code extraction to functional
                programming languages.
            p.
                While being generic blueprint, part of this conceptual model
                was implemented in various languages, other research reports applied.
                This research is founded by Synrc Research Center, Kyiv, Ukraine.
                All works are done under supervision of Pavlo Maslianko,
                National Technical University of Ukraine
                «Igor Sikorsky Kyiv Polytechnic Institute»
                Faculty of Applied Mathematics.

            section
                h1 LANGUAGE FAMILY
            p.
                The thesis is grouped by research areas with their corresponding
                type systems, formal models, type checkers and base libraries.

